Class MoneyMarket

java.lang.Object
com.example.project3.banking.Account

com.example.project3.banking.MoneyMarket
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Account>
public class MoneyMarket extends Savings
Represents a Money Market account, which is a specialized type of Savings account that offers distinct features such as higher interest rates, specific fee structures, and withdrawal limitations. The MoneyMarket account also includes a loyalty status based on the account balance, which influences the applicable interest rate.

    • fee

      public double fee()
      Calculates the fee associated with the MoneyMarket account. The fee is determined based on the account balance and the number of withdrawals. If the account balance meets or exceeds a specified threshold, a standard account fee is not applied; otherwise, a fee is charged. Additional withdrawal fees may apply if the number of withdrawals exceeds the withdrawal threshold.
      Overrides:
      fee in class Savings
      Returns:
      the total fee amount as a double, combining account and withdrawal fees if applicable
